# Gameplay

A song plays over audio. Players press their buttons on beat. Which beats require input is defined per song (tap notes) and communicated visually on the LED strip.

## Beat Input & Scoring

Two judgement tiers (windows from `toxic_game.toml`):

| Result | Timing | Health | LED |
|--------|--------|--------|-----|
| **Perfect** | within ±20 ms of beat | +2 | white flash at player's end |
| **Good** | within ±50 ms (outside perfect) | +1 | white flash at player's end |
| **Error** | miss, or press outside good window | −2 | red flash at player's end |

- Shared health pool starts at **20**, capped at **20**; at **0** → game over
- Both players can have notes on the **same beat** — evaluated independently; two running lights may be active simultaneously
- Ghost taps (no active note) are ignored

## Player 1 (Left Side)

- Notes spawn as a **magenta running light** on the **right end** of the LED strip
- Light travels **right → left**
- Player must press when the light reaches the **left end** of the strip
- Light starts **dark** and **brightens** as it approaches the left end

## Player 2 (Right Side)

- **Mirror of Player 1:** note spawns as a **cyan running light** on the **left end** of the strip
- Light travels **left → right**
- Player must press when the light reaches the **right end** of the strip
- Same brightness ramp: starts dark, brightens as it approaches the hit end

## LED Strip Layout

- Single continuous strip; index 0 = **left end** (Player 1 hit zone), last index = **right end** (Player 2 hit zone)
- Running lights spawn **4 beats (1 bar)** before the hit beat (`lead_time_beats` in config)
- Running lights communicate upcoming notes; end flashes communicate hit/miss feedback

## Timing Concepts

- Songs have: **BPM**, **delay to first beat**, and per-beat **tap note** markers (`bar.beat` text files)
- Tap notes quantized to **quarter notes (4ths)** during recording
- All numeric tuning in **`toxic_game.toml`** — see `config.mdc`
